The paper discusses techniques for transfer learning in the context of materials informatics, which involves applying machine learning to materials science data. The paper focuses on the use of transfer learning to overcome data scarcity, which is a common problem in machine learning. The techniques discussed in the paper are relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and software engineering (cs.SD). However, given the focus on machine learning and data analysis, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The discussion of color classification also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
